before using this project in linux, please consider installing glew headers first :
sudo apt-get install libglew-dev

if you canâ€™t find this package and you dont know which one that provide GL/glew.h 
use this step by step guide :

1)install the apt-file utility 

$ sudo apt-get install apt-file

2)Then, you need to update it's database:

$ apt-file update

3)And, finally, search the file:

$ apt-file find GL/glew.h
emscripten: /usr/share/emscripten/system/include/GL/glew.h
gem-dev: /usr/include/Gem/Gem/glew.h
gem-dev: /usr/include/Gem/Gem/wglew.h
libglew-dev: /usr/include/GL/glew.h
libglew-dev: /usr/include/GL/wglew.h

However a much friendlier way is to use the Ubuntu Packages Search website. 
They have an option to "search the contents of packages" for a specific filename.
